com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.data

Class WZDataEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.data.WZDataEvent

  • public class WZDataEvent
extends Object
    Represents a named event with an optional set of parameters that be sent and received during a broadcast streaming session.

    Usage

    Sending a data event

    During a streaming broadcast session, a data event can be sent using com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.broadcast.WZBroadcast#sendDataEvent(WZDataEvent)

         WZDataMap msgParams = new WZDataMap();
     msgParams.put("UserId", mUser.getId());
     msgParams.put("MessageText", textEntered);

     WZDataEvent chatMsgEvent = new WZDataEvent("onChatMessage", msgParams);

     mWZBroadcast.sendDataEvent("onChatMessage", msgParams);

    Receiving data events

    You can register one or more callbacks to be invoked upon reception of a data event during a streaming broadcast using com.wowza.gocoder.sdk.api.broadcast.WZBroadcast#registerDataEventListener(String, WZDataEvent.EventListener)

    Register an event listener for data event's received with the name "onChatMessage"

          mWZBroadcast.registerDataEventListener("onChatMessage", new WZDataEvent.EventListener() {
          public void onWZDataEvent(WZDataEvent dataEvent) {
               // process event data
          }
      });
